# Mobile Web Patterns

## Navigation

- **Always use `MobileFooter`** (`@/components/layout/mobile-footer`) for primary navigation on mobile viewports — never a sidebar or horizontal top nav
- **Always use `MobileTopNav`** (`@/components/layout/mobile-top-nav`) for page headers on mobile:
  - Back chevron on the **left** (or menu icon for root pages)
  - Page title **centered**
  - **Right slot** left blank unless needed for contextual actions (e.g., share, settings icon)
- **Use the hamburger menu icon** in `MobileTopNav` for secondary navigation on root pages — slides in from the left via `Sheet`
- Use `MobileLayout` (`@/components/layout/mobile-layout`) as the outermost wrapper for pages that need mobile nav/footer

## Sheets and Overlays

- **Use `BottomSheet`** (`@/components/mobile/bottom-sheet`) for contextual actions, filters, confirmations, and pickers — prefer over `Dialog` on mobile
- **Use `SlideInSheet`** (`@/components/mobile/slide-in-sheet`) for sub-pages or detail views that need back navigation — mimics native push/pop navigation
  - Has its own top bar with back chevron (left), title (center), and optional right slot
  - Full-screen on mobile, capped at `sm:max-w-md` on larger viewports

## Animations

- Use animation presets from `@/lib/mobile-animations` for all mobile transitions
- `springConfig` — default spring physics matching iOS feel
- `gentleSpring` — softer transitions for nav headers
- `snappySpring` — quick feedback for taps and tab switches
- `pageTransition` — route change transitions
- `slideInRight` / `slideUp` / `fadeIn` / `scaleIn` — directional entrance variants
- `tapScale` — press feedback for interactive elements
- `staggerContainer` / `staggerItem` — list entrance animations

## Responsive Detection

- Use `useIsMobile()` hook from `@/hooks/use-mobile` for JS-level mobile detection
- Use Tailwind `md:hidden` / `md:block` for CSS-level responsive switching
- Mobile breakpoint: `< 768px`

## Safe Areas (iOS notch / home indicator)

- Use `env(safe-area-inset-top)` for top padding (handled by `MobileTopNav`)
- Use `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` for bottom padding (handled by `MobileFooter`)
- The root layout includes `viewport-fit=cover` to enable safe-area insets

## PWA

- `manifest.json` is generated by `pnpm sync-config` — do not manually edit
- Icons (`icon-192.png`, `icon-512.png`, `apple-touch-icon.png`) are generated from `favicon.svg` by the sync script
- Apple Web App meta tags are set in `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx`

## Do NOT

- Use desktop-only patterns (sidebar nav, hover-dependent menus) as the sole mobile navigation
- Use `Dialog` for mobile actions when `BottomSheet` is more appropriate
- Skip safe-area handling on fixed-position elements
- Hardcode transition durations — use the shared spring configs instead
- Use `framer-motion` import path — use `motion/react` (the v12 package)
